text: Edna Díaz (born 24 April 1985) is a Mexican taekwondo practitioner. She won a gold medal in lightweight at the 2005 World Taekwondo Championships in Madrid, after defeating Su Li-wen in the final. She won a bronze medal at the 2010 Pan American Taekwondo Championships. ==References== ==External links== * Category:1985 births Category:Living people Category:Mexican female taekwondo practitioners Category:World Taekwondo Championships medalists Category:Pan American Taekwondo Championships medalists
